# CRITICAL FIX: Supabase client conflicts causing white screen

## Problem Identified:
Two different Supabase clients are being used:
1. `/src/lib/supabase.ts` - Uses environment variables (VITE_SUPABASE_URL, VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY)
2. `/src/integrations/supabase/client.ts` - Uses hardcoded values

The lib/supabase.ts client throws an error on initialization when env vars are missing:

```
if (!supabaseUrl || !supabaseAnonKey) {
  throw new Error(
    'Supabase URL and anon key must be provided in environment variables. ' +
    'Make sure VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY are set in .env.local'
  );
}
```

Since the environment variables are not set in Vercel, this error is thrown
during module initialization, preventing React from rendering anything.

## Files affected:
